Durban - A 33-year-old man was jailed for 15 years for raping a teenager in 2016 who came to him for karate lessons. Sizwe Jack Mazibuko was sentenced this week in the Madadeni Regional Court. The court heard that the 17-year-old victim had been attending karate lessons with the victim on November 8, 2016, when he raped her. "The accused overpowered, assaulted and raped her. The matter was reported to Madadeni police and the docket was transferred to the Newcastle Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit for investigation," said police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele." Mazibuko was arrested and remained in police custody until his trial. Mbele said the investigation revealed that the accused was released on parole for 18 months before committing the offence. "He was previously convicted for rape and sentenced to life imprisonment." Mbele said that the life sentence was reinstated on the day of his sentence. Daily News  